The paper discusses the use of deep reinforcement learning for dexterous manipulation, which is a problem commonly studied in the field of robotics (cs.RO). The techniques proposed involve extensions to the Deep Deterministic Policy Gradient algorithm, which is a popular algorithm in the field of artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The paper also focuses on improving data efficiency and scalability, which are topics commonly studied in the field of machine learning (cs.LG). The problem of dexterous manipulation often involves analyzing visual input, such as object recognition and tracking, which falls under the category of computer vision (cs.CV). Finally, the paper discusses the potential for training successful policies on real robots, which involves the integration of control and sensing systems, a topic commonly studied in the field of systems and control (cs.SY).
